Constructor Detail

NodeTypeImpl

NodeTypeImpl(EffectiveNodeType ent,
             NodeTypeDef ntd,
             NodeTypeManagerImpl ntMgr,
             NamespaceResolver nsResolver)
Package private constructor

Creates a valid node type instance. We assume that the node type definition is valid and all referenced node types (supertypes, required node types etc.) do exist and are valid.

Parameters:
ent - the effective (i.e. merged and resolved) node type representation
ntd - the definition of this node type
ntMgr - the node type manager associated with this node type
nsResolver - namespace resolver

checkSetPropertyValueConstraints

public static void checkSetPropertyValueConstraints(PropertyDefImpl def,
                                                    InternalValue[] values)
                                             throws javax.jcr.ValueFormatException,
                                                    javax.jcr.nodetype.ConstraintViolationException,
                                                    javax.jcr.RepositoryException
Tests if the value constraints defined in the property definition def are satisfied by the the specified values.

Note that the protected flag is not checked.

Parameters:
def - The definiton of the property
values - An array of InternalValue objects.
Throws:
javax.jcr.ValueFormatException
javax.jcr.nodetype.ConstraintViolationException
javax.jcr.RepositoryException
